key_statement.description:
Receptacles glabrous; pistillate paleae falling (all or the inner together);
        staminate (or bisexual) paleae: bodies ± spatulate (apices scarcely enlarged); central North
        America

Pistillate paleae (compressed, galeate): wings ± erect (and lateral) or inflexed
        (and subapical); receptacles depressed-spheric to obovoid (heights 0.5–1.8 times diams.);
        phyllaries 4–6 (unlike paleae); cypselae: corolla scars ± lateral
